# FunFamily Stock Bot — Project Context

## Purpose
Telegram bot for a private family investment group. Reads and writes an
Excel portfolio file, fetches stock prices from Yahoo Finance, and
responds to queries in a Telegram group chat.

## Excel file
- Filename: Funfamily_Stock_Tracker.xlsx
- Sheet 1 "Deposit Sheet": member deposits and cash balances
- Sheet 2 "Stock Sheet": individual stock positions
- Key columns: Purchaser, Date of Purchase, Ticker, Platform,
  Currency, Original Purchase Price, Holding Price (Any $),
  Gross Holding Value (S$), Net Earning/Loss (S$)
- Members: Shawn Mun, Jasmine
- Platforms: Endowus (unit trusts), IBKR (stocks)

## Yahoo Finance tickers
- iShares S&P 500 (Endowus): 0P0001Q0TW.SI
- TSMC (IBKR): TSM
- MSFT (IBKR): MSFT

## Tech stack
- Python 3.11+
- python-telegram-bot
- yfinance
- openpyxl
- schedule
- python-dotenv

## Bot commands
- /portfolio — full summary, all members
- /mystocks Jasmine — one member's positions
- /update MSFT 395.50 — manually update a price
- /pnl — profit/loss per member
- /help — list commands

## Rules
- All values displayed in SGD
- Show P&L as SGD amount AND percentage
- Keep replies short and mobile-readable
- Daily price auto-update runs at 6pm SGT